  "summary": "Governance is an enabling mechanism, not merely compliance.",
  "body": "Joz views governance as part of system design.\n\nStrong governance creates:\n\n- trust\n- accountability\n- transparency\n- safe autonomy\n- sustainable adoption\n\nWeak governance creates uncertainty and resistance.\n\nIn AI systems, governance should be embedded into architecture through permissions, observability, evaluation, provenance, and human oversight.\n\nTrust should be designed, not assumed.",
